sentences: Henrik Carlsen (born 30 November 1959) is a Danish composer, record producer, singer, and keyboardist.
He was a founding member of Street Beat in 1982 and led it until it was disbanded in 1993.

He was diagnosed with multiple sclerosis in 2001.
He retired from the music business and worked as a school teacher until 2016.
In 2016, he returned to music and released his first solo album "Street Beat Revisited".
In November 2019, Carlsen released the instrumental album "WXYZ", again composing, arranging, performing, and producing all music by himself in his home studio.
